"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The `sns.heatmap` function expects a 2D dataset that can be coerced into an ndarray, typically a matrix of numerical values. The `tips` DataFrame contains categorical columns (like 'sex', 'smoker', 'day', and 'time') and non-numeric columns, which cannot be directly used to create a heatmap. The code does not preprocess the data to ensure that only numeric values are passed to the heatmap function.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< g = sns.heatmap(tips, square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\\n---\\n> g = sns.heatmap(tips.pivot_table(values='tip', index='day', columns='sex'), square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\"\n}"